  "text": "11 We will use the existence of a time-like vectorfield T such that (3.1) holds to prove that g is in fact a perturbation of the Kerr metric in the entire domain of dependence of Σ∩{r ≥ R}, for R sufficiently large. The transformation to \"comoving\" coordinates of Appendix A in [CITATION_1] then shows that (D, g) is positive mass space-time, as discussed in Section 4.2, and in particular satisfies the assumptions of Theorem 4.2.",
